<title>DENMARK: Superfos ups Phoenix bid.</title>
<headline>Superfos ups Phoenix bid.</headline>
<dateline>COPENHAGEN 1997-02-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Danish construction and chemicals group Superfos said on Friday it was raising its offer for local roadbuilder Phoenix to 730 Danish crowns per A-share and 655 crowns per B-share.  </p>
<p>Business magazine Borsens Nyhedsmagasin on Friday valued Phoenix at 900 million crowns.</p>
<p>Phoenix directors have indicated that their recommendation will be based not on money alone, but also on continued autonomy for the roadbuilding firm and minimal layoffs for its employees.</p>
<p>--Steve Weizman, Copenhagen newsroom +45 33969650</p>
